<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 5:06AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Rapidly Deteriorating Roads This Morning...
The rain will slowly transition to light snow, sleet and freezing
rain early this morning. The overall intensity will decrease.
However, arctic air is now advancing across the Saginaw Valley and
thumb region and will reach the I-69 corridor from Owosso to
Lapeer between 7 AM and 8 AM. The rapid drop in temperatures over
the wet roads will cause a rapid freezing. This will be first
noticeable on bridges and overpasses. Drivers are urged to prepare
for icy roads and pedestrians should be prepared for icy paved
surfaces.</description>
